-- Jeter, Yankees Reach Three-Year Contract Agreement, New York Times Reports
-- B y   S y l v i a   W i e r
-- 2010-12-04T22:14:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-04/jeter-yankees-reach-three-year-contract-agreement-new-york-times-reports.html
Derek Jeter and the New York Yankees
have agreed on a three-year contract worth $15 million to
$17 million annually, the New York Times reported, citing an
unidentified person in baseball briefed on the matter.  The contract has an option on a fourth year, the newspaper
said. Jeter will remain the highest-paid shortstop in Major
League Baseball, the Times said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at 
 swier@bloomberg.net  